EC2(Elastic Computing Cloud)  - Infrastructure as a Service

Real Life Analogy
Without EC2 (Old Way):
  Buy a house → Very expensive
   You own it → You maintain it
   Fixed size → Can't change easily

With EC2 (AWS Way):
   Rent a hotel room → Pay only what you use
   AWS maintains it → No headache
   Change size anytime → Flexible!

Type	    Use Case	Example
t3.micro	Small apps, testing	Free tier
t3.medium	Medium workload	Dev environment
t3.large	Production apps	Your AOM server
r5.xlarge	Memory heavy	Large databases
c5.xlarge	CPU heavy	Computing tasks

Point 1️⃣ — EBS is Storage for EC2
EC2 by itself has NO permanent storage!

Without EBS:
EC2 starts  → Data stored temporarily
EC2 stops   → ❌ ALL DATA LOST!

With EBS:
EC2 starts  → Data stored on EBS
EC2 stops   → ✅ Data still safe on EBS!
EC2 starts again → Data still there ✅



Point 1️⃣ — ELB Distributes Traffic to EC2
Without ELB:
1000 users → Only 1 EC2 → 💥 Server crashes!

With ELB:
1000 users → ELB → EC2 #1 (333 users) ✅
                 → EC2 #2 (333 users) ✅
                 → EC2 #3 (334 users) ✅
All servers balanced — No crash! ✅
